<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 28 at 7:28PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER STORM WARNING IS IN EFFECT TONIGHT...
WEATHER...
* Light snow continues across the area while gradually increasing
intensity and areal coverage as heavier bands move in from the
west.
* Additional accumulation up to 1 inch is expected from 730 PM to
1030 PM with locally near 2 inches possible in the Tri Cities
area.
IMPACTS...
* Snow accumulating at increasing rate will lead to hazardous
road conditions, particularly on bridges, exit ramps and
overpasses.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for the variable
driving conditions by reducing speed and allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
